          "title": "QriptoCENT Revenue Models for Agentic Commerce",
          "type": "article",
          "format": "article",
          "content": {},
          "excerpt": "From QriptoMedia to data markets, a tour of monetisation strategies that only work at Q¢ scale.",
          "placement": {
            "tab": "exec",
            "imageX": 50,
            "imageY": 50,
            "section": "21knowdz",
            "position": 3,
            "imageScale": 100,
            "imagePosition": "center"
          },
          "modalities": {
            "link": {
              "url": "https://qripto.net/exec/revenue-models",
              "allow_embed": false
            },
            "read": {
              "text": "# QriptoCENT revenue models for agentic commerce\n\nQriptoCENT enables revenue models that are either impossible or uneconomic on traditional rails.\n\n## QriptoMedia\n\n- **Per panel or per chapter payments** in comics and graphic novels\n- **Micro tips** for artists, writers and animators\n- **Dynamic pricing** where Aigents adjust Q¢ amounts based on engagement\n\n## Data markets with COYN\n\n- Organisations can mint COYN representing rights over datasets\n- Aigents pay in QriptoCENT whenever they access or derive value from those datasets\n- Fine grained audit trails show who used what, when and for how much\n\n## High frequency trading and agentic portfolios\n\n- Aigent MoneyPenny can run strategies denominated in Q¢ with very small positions\n- Micro rebalancing and hedging becomes feasible without racking up fees\n\n## Micro subscriptions and streams\n\n- Instead of monthly subscriptions, services can stream Q¢ per minute or per request\n- Users can cap spend and Aigents ensure value per Q¢ remains acceptable\n\n## Strategic takeaway\n\nBy embracing QriptoCENT, enterprises can match revenue mechanics to actual usage patterns, unlocking latent value that was previously stranded below the threshold of economic viability.\n",
              "duration": "7 min read"
            }
          },
