          "title": "Deploying QriptoCENT Services to QubeBase",
          "type": "tutorial",
          "format": "article",
          "content": {},
          "excerpt": "A DevOps-oriented workflow for testing and deploying QriptoCENT-aware applications on QubeBase.",
          "placement": {
            "tab": "dev",
            "imageX": 50,
            "imageY": 50,
            "section": "21knowdz",
            "position": 5,
            "imageScale": 100,
            "imagePosition": "center"
          },
          "modalities": {
            "link": {
              "url": "https://qripto.net/docs/qubebase/devops",
              "allow_embed": false
            },
            "read": {
              "text": "# Deploying QriptoCENT services to QubeBase\n\nOnce your QriptoCENT logic works in a local sandbox, the next step is to get it into a repeatable test and deployment pipeline. QubeBase is the hub for storing and querying iQubes and app state.\n\n## Environments and configuration\n\nStart by defining at least three environments:\n\n- Local development\n- Shared staging\n- Production\n\nFor each environment you will configure:\n\n- QubeBase connection details\n- AigentiQ endpoints and keys\n- QriptoCENT network configuration (for example, testnet vs mainnet RUNE backing)\n\nStore these in environment specific config files or secret stores.\n\n## Migration strategies\n\nAlthough iQubes are flexible, you will still need to manage schema like changes:\n\n- New iQube templates for payment or entitlement types\n- Additional metadata fields for QriptoCENT pricing rules\n- New indexes and views in QubeBase\n\nAdopt a migration tool or simple versioned scripts so that all environments can be brought up to the same state in a controlled way.\n\n## Automated tests for Q¢ flows\n\nFor QriptoCENT-aware services, tests should cover:\n\n- Happy path Q¢ payments and entitlements\n- Failure modes when policies or limits block a payment\n- Behaviour when Aigents are temporarily unavailable\n\nWhere feasible, run a suite of integration tests against a QubeBase staging environment before promoting to production.\n\n## Deployment pipeline\n\nUse your preferred CI system to:\n\n- Run unit tests on every commit\n- Run integration tests on merges to main\n- Build and deploy containers or serverless bundles to your runtime\n- Apply QubeBase migrations and configuration in an ordered fashion\n\nTag releases when you change anything that touches QriptoCENT logic so you can correlate on chain and off chain behaviour later.\n\n## Observability and rollback\n\nEnsure you have:\n\n- Metrics for QriptoCENT volume, error rates and latency\n- Dashboards that can slice data by tenant, Aigent or capability\n- A clear rollback path if a release causes unexpected behaviour in Q¢ flows\n\nBy treating QriptoCENT as a first class concern in your DevOps practice, you protect both users and partners while still moving fast.\n",
              "duration": "7 min read"
            }
          },
